      "content": "Candidate A communicates clearly and professionally. They use constructive language, offering genuine empathy and constructive solutions, which make them sound confident and well-prepared for a client-facing role.\n\nCandidate B's communication style is less formal; they utilize a casual tone characterized by contractions and is a less structured approach to problem-solving. Although they attempt to empathize with the customer, their response may come across as too informal for a professional customer success role. It may be perceived as less confident and less prepared for handling customer complaints compared to Candidate A.",
